I've heard people saying it wasn't Rodgers' fault they lost and they keep blaming it on everything else
Rodgers went:
-Scoreless in the first half
-Most of his yards/TDs in garbage time already down 27 or down 17
-2 interceptions
-Fumbled twice but lucky as hell that the 49er defense didnt jump on the ball fast enough
-ran once for 0 yards


Obviously he can't play defense, but that doesn't matter when you can't score once in the first 30 minutes. You can't continue to win games, especially big games against an incredibly tough opponent, if you take 35 minutes to score one time.

snippet.textDisplay:
To me Kevin King should be more their 3rd or 4th option at CB. He gets beat far too often because he does what he wants during the play.

Defensively we clearly have some major areas to address. Alexander needs to be our number two CB. We need someone who can lock up with other teams number one and not get beat.

We need better interior linemen. We need better LB to add to Martinez if they resign him.

Offensively we need to make Valdeer the highest paid back up and find a true number two WR. Allison needs to be gone. MVS gone. Lazard should be #3 option. Aaron Jones is a good shifty back but to me is more of a highlight player like Tyler Ervin. We need a Henry type back to play Green Bay Packers football. Smash mouth football. Pound them and let Aaron do his thing. So many areas to address. Really wish we had done something prior to the trade deadline. We showed up in the 2nd half yesterday. With a few key positions addressed. We could have pulled the upset that Kansas City did to the Texans
